  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "Honsou returns to repay his debt to the Ultramarines. He gathers a Skull Harvest coalition — Iron Warriors warbands, Chaos-tainted renegades, and the Khornate cultist horde called the Bloodborn — and drives deep into Ultramar, striking at Calth and the worlds adjacent to Macragge itself. Chapter Master Marneus Calgar mobilises the full chapter. Captain Cato Sicarius leads the 2nd Company; Captain Uriel Ventris fights with the 4th; Chief Librarian Tigurius reads the warp-tides; Chaplain Cassius rallies the relief force; the renegade Ardaric Vaanes is among Honsou's Astartes lieutenants. The novel runs the siege at sector scale across Calth's surface as set-piece battles. Honsou's blood-debt is paid in chapter blood and chapter mourning; the series-finale to the first Ventris six-book arc closes with Honsou wounded but missing rather than confirmed dead.",
